com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.util.parsers
Class TermParserTools

java.lang.Object
  com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.util.parsers.TermParserTools

public final class TermParserTools
extends java.lang.Object

This class contains utility methods for parsers which can be used to in various ways process Terms in the process of test case generation.

christopher

binaryFunctions

private static final java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.String> binaryFunctions
The sort names of the various binary functions represented in the KeY Term hierarchy. Note that equality is not a part of this list, since it is represented by its own operational type Equality.

getVariableNameForTerm

public static java.lang.String getVariableNameForTerm(de.uka.ilkd.key.logic.Term term)
Retrieves the short-hand name of the variable a given Term represents. For example, in the Term 

 com.example.MyClass::$myVariable,

the returned shorthand is myVariable.

Parameters:
term - the Term to process
Returns:
the short-hand name of the variable represented by the Term. If the Term does not represent a variable, the regular toString output of the Terms Operator instance is returned.

resolveIdentifierString

public static java.lang.String resolveIdentifierString(de.uka.ilkd.key.logic.Term term,
                                                       java.lang.String separator)
Generate an identifier String for a variable. Such an identifier is used in order to uniquely distinguish an instance of a ModelVariable.

If the variable is defined by a SortDependingFunction, the identifier will be generated by recursively exploring the nesting hierarchy this variable is a part of.

Parameters:
term - the Term representing the variable
Returns:
the identifier String.
See Also:
Model
